race.comment: If ZOUCAT (8) brings her best form she looks the horse to beat. Good effort two back when third over 1300m at Canberra but was disappointing last time. On a six-day back-up and is generally reliable so worth another chance. CASINO SHAW (5) hasn't been all that far away in two runs since a two-month let-up. Capable of further improvement with the application of blinkers for the first time. SPIRITUAL STAR (9) and FARSAIN (10) are first starters from highly respected stables in this region. Any positive market moves for either runner should be respected. LIAMENA AVENUE (1) resumes. Didn't show much last prep but is a recent Kembla trial winner and this is a shallow affair so a bright return will not surprise.
